OL,3,CHillsborough Law campaigners 'withdraw
OL,4,Csupport' for draft bill
OL,6,FHillsborough Law Now has said
OL,7,F"families cannot accept a law that
OL,8,Fallows the heads of the security
OL,9,Fservices to hide serious failures
OL,10,Fbehind a vague claim of national
OL,11,Fsecurity".
OL,13,FThe group continued: "It's time for
OL,14,Fthe Prime Minister to deliver on the
OL,15,Fpromise he made when he looked the
OL,16,Fbereaved of Hillsborough in the eye
OL,17,Fand use this pause to lay down the law
OL,18,Fto Whitehall and the security
OL,19,Fservices."
